<p>

Where n is the normalized vector of the hit subtracted from the center. Both are added by 0.5 to properly center it on the 2d image. As tan<sup>-1</sup>(<sup>x</sup>/<sub>y</sub>) is returns numbers in the domain of (-π, π). The texture mapping for the cylinder maps the curved portion of the cylinder to the 2d image and maps the top of the cylinder to the top of the 2d image.
</p>
